:{{see|telescopium}}

==English==
===Etymology===
Named by the French [[astronomer]] Nicolas Louis de Lacaille in 1763. From later {{L.}} ''[[telescopium]]'', a "[[telescope]]"

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Telescopium'''

#{{constellation}}: A small faint [[constellation]] of the [[southern]] [[winter]] sky, said to resemble a [[telescope]]. It lies south of the [[constellation]] of [[Corona Australis]].

